 : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `f : α → β` be a function from a linear order `α` to a topological space `β`, and\nlet `a : α`. The limit strictly to the right of `f` at `a`, denoted with `rightLim f a`, is defined\nby using the order topology on `α`. If `a` is isolated to its right or the function has no right\nlimit, we use `f a` instead to guarantee a good behavior in most cases. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Order/LeftRightLim.html#Function.rightLim","kind":"def","line":57,"name":"Function.rightLim","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Order/LeftRightLim.lean#L57-L62"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">noncomputable def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Order/LeftRightLim.html#Function.leftLim\"><span class=\"name\">Function</span>.<span class=\"name\">leftLim</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">β</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Defs/LinearOrder.html#LinearOrder\">LinearOrder</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">f</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">α</span> → <span class=\"fn\">β</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <span class=\"fn\">α</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">β</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Let `f : α → β` be a function from a linear order `α` to a topological space `β`, and\nlet `a : α`. The limit strictly to the left of `f` at `a`, denoted with `leftLim f a`, is defined\nby using the order topology on `α`. If `a` is isolated to its left or the function has no left\nlimit, we use `f a` instead to guarantee a good behavior in most cases. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Order/LeftRightLim.html#Function.leftLim","kind":"def","line":47,"name":"Function.leftLim","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Topology/Order/LeftRightLim.lean#L47-L55"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.Order.LeftRight","Mathlib.Topology.Order.Monotone","Mathlib.Topology.Separation.Regular"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Order.LeftRightLim"}